Sentencas: Crystallographic structural changes were investigated for Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta, an electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Investigation of the high-temperature redox chemistry of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ via in situ neutron diffraction

Sentencas: The samples of this material were heated and cooled in wet hydrogen and wet oxygen atmospheres, to simulate the reducing and oxidizing conditions experienced under actual fuel cell operating conditions, and their structures and oxygen contents were determined using in situ powder neutron diffraction.
Titulo: Investigation of the high-temperature redox chemistry of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ via in situ neutron diffraction

Sentencas: The existence of a reversible tetragonal to cubic phase transition was established to occur between room temperature and 400 degrees C, both on heating and cooling in either oxygen or hydrogen.
Titulo: Investigation of the high-temperature redox chemistry of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ via in situ neutron diffraction

Sentencas: The oxygen content reaches a low value of 5.50(2) at 850 degrees C in wet hydrogen.
Titulo: Investigation of the high-temperature redox chemistry of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ via in situ neutron diffraction

Sentencas: Excellent correlations are observed between the oxygen content of the structure and the conductivities reported in the literature.
Titulo: Investigation of the high-temperature redox chemistry of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ via in situ neutron diffraction
